  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a steady-state single-phase incompressible RANS formulation with the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation. Non-Newtonian blood rheology under pulsatile inflow conditions — a physically real phenomenon present during clinical CPB operation — is excluded from the model; the fluid is treated as Newtonian with a fixed dynamic viscosity of 3.5 mPa·s. The sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to this rheological simplification was studied informally by the modelling team but results were not formally documented and no dedicated sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study was conducted. Validation activities were performed exclusively under steady-flow bench conditions using a Newtonian blood analogue, so the validation evidence does not probe the impact of the non-Newtonian pulsatile exclusion on the quantity of interest.",
