      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating envelope span the COU operating points; fluid and boundary conditions are representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at flow rates and speeds spanning the COU envelope (3–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). Newtonian analogue viscosity matched to mean clinical blood viscosity. The validation activities do not include pulsatile inflow conditions representative of clinical CPB; however, the modelling team notes informally that sensitivity to this simplification was studied and considered acceptable. No formal sensitivity analysis report or fidelity trade study is available to substantiate this assertion."
    },
    {
