      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup by a second analyst; checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup independently reviewed by a second CFD analyst using institutional checklist CL-CFD-02. Boundary conditions, material properties, solver settings, and UDF parameters verified. No discrepancies found. Review documented in memo RM-2023-07."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified against literature benchmarks for rotating blood-contacting devices; hemolysis correlation applicability documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmarks for centrifugal blood pump flows (Fraser et al. 2011, Hariharan et al. 2018). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis correlation applied within its documented exposure-time and shear-stress validity range. The model is formulated as steady-state single-phase Newtonian; non-Newtonian shear-thinning behaviour of blood and pulsatile flow dynamics are excluded. The rationale for this exclusion references an informal internal sensitivity study, but no fidelity trade study quantifying the impact of these omissions on RH index prediction has been formally documented or linked as evidence."
    },
